    <section data-max-lines="5" class="show-more-less-html">
        <div class="show-more-less-html__markup show-more-less-html__markup--clamp-after-5
            relative overflow-hidden">
          <p><strong>Title: Data Analyst - Business Insights &amp; Analytics</strong></p><p><strong>Location - Mumbai</strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>OUR STORY:</strong></p><p>JioSaavn is South Asia’s leading audio streaming service to access, discover, and listen to favorite songs &amp; Podcasts across languages and genres. We blend digital technology, data analysis (which we have affectionately coined Music Science), and strong, fearless business acumen to reach all corners of the globe. Our award-winning mobile products, partnerships, innovations, and thought leadership have been featured in some of the world’s leading publications, from The New York Times to The Wall Street Journal, The Economic Times to Forbes, and many more.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>OUR CULTURE:</strong></p><p>At JioSaavn, we ignite passion and performance to work towards a collective goal: creating the perfect mobile entertainment ecosystem that delivers the best possible music experience to millions of listeners around the world. Our default mode is that of perpetual innovation. Together, we form a concerted rhythm that goes beyond borders. We don't just go with the flow, we create it.</p><p>JioSaavn offers a dynamic and unconventional work environment, full of fun wholesome experiences. We believe creativity and technology blend like sweet melodies. When you choose JioSaavn, you join a diverse world of high-caliber techies, artists, and inventors hailing from companies like Yahoo!, Twitter, LinkedIn, Google, Qualcomm, HBO, Microsoft, Flipkart, Amazon, Paytm, Quikr, etc.</p><p>Our value-based, people-first work culture is about empowering every individual in our team to be a catalyst for change in this dynamic digital world. Every day is an opportunity to bring your vision to life, and to expand, learn and grow. No idea is left unconsidered. No voice is left unheard.</p><p>JioSaavn prides itself on being an equal-opportunity employer. We have committed ourselves to creating a safe environment with fair and equal access and opportunities, sans discrimination. We encourage everyone to be open to experiences and perspectives beyond their normal; divergent thinkers create differentiated products and even better music.</p><p>If our vibe matches with yours, we'd love to hear from you.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>ROLE:</strong></p><p>JioSaavn is seeking an analytically driven and open-minded individual to join our rapidly growing global team of entrepreneurs. The Business Insights team acts as a trusted business adviser to teams across the company and senior leadership. This team is responsible for analyzing high-priority business challenges and for proposing solutions based on thorough quantitative analysis.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><ul><li>The role will be an integral member of the Business Insights team and will be responsible for providing support and analysis across the breadth of work provided by the team</li></ul><p><strong><em>Examples of such responsibilities include:</em></strong></p><ul><li>Using a combination of Python and SQL to support data analysis on a variety of cross-functional projects</li><li>Creating and regularly updating data dashboards to help define and measure progress toward KPIs across key business focus areas</li><li>Identifying opportunities for continuous improvement and automation of tasks using Python and SQL where relevant</li><li>Identifying ways in which complex and ambiguous business problems can be solved systematically and objectively with the help of data and market research</li><li>Analyzing internal and external data to uncover trends in user behavior and the industry as a whole, influencing product, content, and marketing roadmaps</li><li>Creating presentations for the executive team summarizing key insights and action items derived through robust research and analyses</li><li>Working closely with several departments across the company including Data Engineering, Product, Marketing, Strategy &amp; Operations, and Content, to support data-driven decision-making</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s or higher degree in Statistics, Math, Data Analytics, Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, or other related quantitative field</li><li>0-1 years of experience working in a highly analytical environment providing data insights</li><li>Exceptional data querying skills</li><li>Relevant experience working with SQL to query data as well as to build data tables</li><li>Relevant experience working with Python (or R) for data analysis, visualization, and automation</li><li>Relevant experience of experience with data visualization tools such as Looker Studio / Tableau</li><li>Ability to effectively articulate complex ideas simply and intuitively through presentations to a diverse group of stakeholders</li><li>Extremely comfortable with Excel, PowerPoint / Keynote</li><li>Passion and deep understanding of the technology, media, and entertainment space</li><li>Ability to work collaboratively and build effective team relationships to solve and operationalize complex business problems.</li><li>An entrepreneurial, “roll up your sleeves” attitude and willingness to perform tasks with a range of difficulty from routine tasks to preparing analysis for senior management.</li><li>Effective in working autonomously to “get things done” and taking the initiative to anticipate the needs of teams and senior management</li></ul>
        </div>
